article.headline: Missouri St. 69, Tulsa 64
article.story: SPRINGFIELD, Mo. -- Kyle Weems racked up a double-double, scoring 17 points and grabbing 12 rebounds, to help Missouri State pull out a 69-64 win in overtime against Tulsa on Saturday night. The Bears (4-0) were down 56-53 with 8 seconds left in regulation when Anthony Downing sank a 3-pointer to force overtime. Missouri State took the early lead in extra play, but the Golden Hurricane (4-3) quickly caught up. Tulsa went ahead on a tip-in by Joe Richard with 1:40 left. The lead didn't last long. Weems hit a 3-pointer just 12 seconds later to give the Missouri State a 65-64 advantage. Tulsa did not score again. Caleb Patterson scored a team-high 19 points for the Bears while Jarmar Gulley added 16. Jordan Clarkson finished with a game-high 23 points for Tulsa, Scottie Haralson added 15 and Kodi Maduka grabbed a double-double with 11 points and a game-high 13 rebounds.
